Source: plymouth-theme-nhos-gnome
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Rob Dyke (robdykedotcom) <robdyke@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.4

Package: plymouth-theme-nhos-gnome-logo
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, plymouth, plymouth-label
Provides: plymouth-theme
Breaks: plymouth (<< 0.9.2-3ubuntu1~),
Description: graphical boot animation and logger - nhos-gnome-logo theme
 Plymouth is an application that runs very early in the boot process
 (even before the root filesystem is mounted!) that provides a graphical
 boot animation while the boot process happens in the background.
 .
 This package contains the default nhos-gnome-logo theme.

Package: plymouth-theme-nhos-gnome-text
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, plymouth, plymouth-theme-ubuntu-text
Provides: plymouth-theme
Replaces: plymouth (<< 0.8.1-1~)
Breaks: plymouth (<< 0.9.2-3ubuntu1~),
Description: graphical boot animation and logger - nhos-gnome-text theme
 Plymouth is an application that runs very early in the boot process
 (even before the root filesystem is mounted!) that provides a graphical
 boot animation while the boot process happens in the background.
 .
 This package contains the default nhos-gnome-text text theme used when no
 support for a graphical theme is found on your system.
